.TH "drm_gem_map_dma_buf" 9 "drm_gem_map_dma_buf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_gem_map_dma_buf \- map_dma_buf implementation for GEM
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct sg_table *" drm_gem_map_dma_buf
.BI "(struct dma_buf_attachment *attach "  ","
.BI "enum dma_data_direction dir "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "attach" 12
attachment whose scatterlist is to be returned
.IP "dir" 12
direction of DMA transfer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calls \fIdrm_gem_object_funcs.get_sg_table\fP and then maps the scatterlist. This
can be used as the \fIdma_buf_ops.map_dma_buf\fP callback. Should be used together
with \fBdrm_gem_unmap_dma_buf\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
sg_table containing the scatterlist to be returned; returns ERR_PTR
on error. May return -EINTR if it is interrupted by a signal.
